


---

## Chrome Extension — Flavor-Specific Notes

### Architecture

Chrome MV3 service worker + popup. Built with esbuild (not webpack).

### Key Files

- `manifest.json` — Chrome MV3 manifest (permissions, service worker entry)
- `src/background/service-worker.ts` — Extension entry point
- `src/core/settings.ts` — `SETTINGS_SCHEMA` single source of truth
- `src/popup/popup.html` — Popup UI
- `scripts/esbuild-*.mjs` — Build scripts (dev with sourcemaps, prod minified + metafile)
- `scripts/package.mjs` — Cross-platform zip packaging (archiver)
- `scripts/verify.mjs` — Full local CI pipeline (lint + build + test + E2E)
- `scripts/preflight.mjs` — Pre-release checks (verify + manifest + dist integrity)

### Commands

| Command | Purpose | Speed |
|---------|---------|-------|
| `npm test` | Run all unit tests | ~15s |
| `npm run build:dev` | Dev build with source maps | ~10s |
| `npm run build:prod` | Production build (minified, metafile) | ~30s |
| `npm run package` | Build + cross-platform zip for CWS | ~35s |
| `npm run verify` | Full verification (lint + build + tests) | ~2min |
| `npm run verify -- --no-e2e` | Verify without E2E tests | ~1min |
| `npm run preflight` | Pre-release checks (verify + manifest + dist) | ~3min |
| `npm run test:e2e` | Playwright E2E against real Chrome | ~1min |
| `npm run sync-version` | Sync package.json version -> manifest.json | instant |

### Chrome API Mocking

jsdom has no `chrome.*`. Every test touching Chrome APIs must mock them.
See `src/test/setup.ts` for the global mock loaded via vitest setupFiles.

### CWS Naming Constraints

Chrome Web Store rejects packages with underscore-prefixed directories (`__tests__`, `__mocks__`). Tests live as colocated `*.test.ts` / `*.spec.ts` files; shared test setup is in `src/test/`.

### Settings

Never hardcode a setting key. Always reference `SETTINGS_SCHEMA` in `src/core/settings.ts`.

### Version Sync

`scripts/sync-version.mjs` keeps `package.json` and `manifest.json` versions in sync.
Always bump in `package.json` first, then run `npm run sync-version`.

### E2E Testing (Playwright)

E2E tests live in `e2e/` and use a custom fixture (`e2e/fixtures/extension.ts`) that launches Chromium with the extension loaded from `dist/`. Extensions cannot run headless — CI uses `xvfb` on Linux. The `e2e.yml` workflow runs automatically on PRs that touch `src/`, `e2e/`, or `manifest.json`.
